article.description: Xavier Lundy scored 20 points and Norville Carey had his first double-double of the season to lift Rider to a 71-69 win over Siena on Monday night.
article.headline: Rider overtakes Siena in second half for 71-69 win
article.linkText: Rider overtakes Siena in second half for 71-69 win
article.story: LAWRENCEVILLE, N.J. -- Xavier Lundy scored 20 points and Norville Carey had his first double-double of the season to lift Rider to a 71-69 win over Siena on Monday night. Rider (4 3, 1-1 Metro Atlantic) overtook Siena late in the game with an 11-3 spurt that put the Broncs up 69-68 with 2:22 left. Lundy, Carey and Jimmie Taylor all had at least one bucket during the run. Taylor stretched the advantage by going 1 for 2 from the line but Siena cut it to one with 10 seconds left when Marquis Wright split a pair of free throws. Carey also went 1 for 2 from the line, then rebounded a missed 3-pointer from Siena's Nico Clareth to seal it. Carey finished with 14 points and a career-high-tying 13 rebounds, and Kahlil Thomas had 11 rebounds. Lavon Long led Siena (3-6, 1-1) with 19 points and Brett Bisping had 15 rebounds.
